    "East :Starting from the North East corner from Yarada Village and turns towards South side passing through Bay of Bengal Sea shore up to Gangavaram Container Yard and continue along the coast of the Bay of Bengal up to the Eastern corner Compound Wall of the Visakhapatnam Steel Plant. South :Starting from the Eastern corner Compound Wall of the Visakhapatnam Steel Plant runs along the Compound Wall of the Visakhapatnam Steel Plant up to the Tower where the distance marking no.597 is marked on the Compound Wall. West : Starting from the above point and turns towards North side and runs along Compound Wall of the Visakhapatnam Steel Plant towards passing through the Gangavaram Main Gate and up to the Gangavaram Junction on BC Roadand runs along the road to Gangavaram Village upto the Kongapalem Junction and turn towards North side runs along the road leading to the Venkannapalem and Kongapalem villages and turn towards North side at the drain before the Sri Rama Mandiram, Venkannapalem and runs along the drain passing abutting the Sri SriSriPydi Thalli AmmavariAalayam, Venkannapalem and runs along the drain up to the APIIC Compound Wall and turn towards the East side and runs along the Southern boundary of the Yathapalem Village and turn towards the North side and runs along the Eastern boundary of the Yathapalem Village and runs on top of the Sy.No.274 of Pedagantyada Hill and continues till the Yedugulla point and continues on hill top up to the Eastern boundary of the Ashok Nagar and ends at the building block no.18 excluding the building blocks 18, 19, 20, 21, 26 and 27. North : Starting from the North-Western boundary of the Vambay Colony building Block No.18 and turn towards East side excluding the building blocks 18, 19, 20, 21, 26 and 27 and runs along the top of the Sy.No.274 Hill passing through the Southern boundary of the Dolphin Hill up to the junction where the southern road abutting to Sunrise Holiday Home (Navy) and Dolphin Hill road meets and runs up to the Yarada Village meets at the Starting Point"
