  "east: starting from survey no. 41 of koppaka village at the north-eastern corner, the boundary proceeds southwards along the gvmc boundary, crosses the nh-16 road at sirasapalli, continues along the boundary of rajupalem village, crosses the railway track, and thereafter crosses the yeleru canal. it further proceeds along the eastern boundary of rajupalem village and finally reaches survey no. 159 of valluru village at the south- eastern corner. south: starting from survey no. 159 of valluru village at the south-eastern corner, the boundary proceeds westwards along the gvmc boundary, adjoining the boundary of thotada village, and continues along the sharada river branch canal (ava canal) up to survey no. 376 of the thotada village revenue boundary. west: starting from survey no. 376 of the thotada village revenue boundary, the boundary proceeds northwards along the thotada road up to the anjaneya swamy temple located near the nh-16 road. from there, it turns eastwards and reaches the karrivariveedhi arch. thereafter, it proceeds northwards along karrivari veedhi road and over koneru dibba up to the chinna ramaswamy temple. from there, it continues in the north- eastern direction along the dasari gedda road, passing the ambedkar statue and reaching the entrance of sattamma thalli temple, where it turns westwards towards the gnt road. it then proceeds via balakrishna bus stand up to the ring road junction and again turns northwards near the fish market, continuing along the fish market lane, neyyila veedhi, and yarravari veedhi up to pillavarigorch. from there, it proceeds eastwards along pillavariveedhi up to the ntr market ring road. thereafter, the boundary continues northwards along the market road and the drainage canal up to the railway track. north: starting from the railway track at the north-western corner, the boundary proceeds eastwards, crossing the bridge on sabbavaram road and continuing along the railway track. it further crosses the six-lane road bridge and continues along the railway track up to the koppaka nh-16 road bridge. from there, it turns eastwards at the yeleru canal culvert and proceeds northwards through golagam revenue survey nos. 265 and 266, continuing along the gvmc boundary. thereafter, it proceeds eastwards along the revenue boundary of kondakoppaka village and finally ends at survey no. 41 of koppaka village at the north-eastern corner": 107,
